%description:

D3/D5(a) proving test, shape (i)+(iii-switch): a processing-delay layer is
enabled inside a switch's bridging layer. Unlike the plain EthernetSwitch
(whose default "bridging" submodule is MacRelayUnit/Ieee8021dRelay, which
has no such slot), TsnSwitch already switches "bridging" to the modular
"BridgingLayer" (inet/linklayer/ethernet/common/BridgingLayer.ned), which
has an optional "processingDelayLayer: <default(\"\")> like
IProcessingDelayLayer" submodule slot spliced directly into its pipeline
(upperLayerIn -> processingDelayLayer -> directionReverser -> ... and back).
This test uses a zero-delay/pass-through "ProcessingDelayLayer" instance
(ingress/egress PacketDelayer, delay = 0s) there -- no new NED is invented.

This file's ini has two configs:
- [Config Baseline]: bridging.processingDelayLayer.typename = "" (the
  @omittedTypename mechanism substitutes OmittedProcessingDelayLayer, a
  pure pass-through)
- [Config WithProcessingDelay]: bridging.processingDelayLayer.typename =
  "ProcessingDelayLayer" with delay = 0s on both the ingress and egress
  packet delayers

Both configs were run manually and produce IDENTICAL app-level output
(client sends 6 UDP packets -- the 6th right at the sim-time-limit, never
delivered, in both configs alike -- server receives 5); this test commits
the WithProcessingDelay variant to prove insertion doesn't change
application-visible behavior.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%extraargs: -c WithProcessingDelay
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
network = Test
ned-path = .;../../../../src
sim-time-limit = 5ms
cmdenv-express-mode = false

#omnetpp 5.0 - 5.1 compatibility:
eventlog-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.elog"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sca"
output-vector-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.vec"
snapshot-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sna"

*.client.hasTcp = false
*.client.hasSctp = false
*.client.hasQuic = false
*.server.hasTcp = false
*.server.hasSctp = false
*.server.hasQuic = false
*.switch.eth[*].bitrate = 100Mbps

*.client.numApps = 1
*.client.app[0].typename = "UdpSourceApp"
*.client.app[0].source.packetLength = 100B
*.client.app[0].source.productionInterval = 1ms
*.client.app[0].io.destAddress = "server"
*.client.app[0].io.destPort = 1000

*.server.numApps = 1
*.server.app[0].typename = "UdpSinkApp"
*.server.app[0].io.localPort = 1000

[Config Baseline]
*.switch.bridging.processingDelayLayer.typename = ""

[Config WithProcessingDelay]
*.switch.bridging.processingDelayLayer.typename = "ProcessingDelayLayer"
*.switch.bridging.processingDelayLayer.ingress.delay = 0s
*.switch.bridging.processingDelayLayer.egress.delay = 0s

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: test.ned

import inet.node.inet.StandardHost;
import inet.node.tsn.TsnSwitch;
import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv4.Ipv4NetworkConfigurator;

network Test
{
    submodules:
        configurator: Ipv4NetworkConfigurator {
            @display("p=300,100");
        }
        client: StandardHost {
            @display("p=100,250");
        }
        switch: TsnSwitch {
            @display("p=300,250");
        }
        server: StandardHost {
            @display("p=500,250");
        }
    connections:
        client.ethg++ <--> { datarate = 100Mbps; delay = 10us; } <--> switch.ethg++;
        switch.ethg++ <--> { datarate = 100Mbps; delay = 10us; } <--> server.ethg++;
}

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: results/WithProcessingDelay-0.sca
scalar Test.client.app[0].io "packets sent" 6
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: results/WithProcessingDelay-0.sca
scalar Test.server.app[0].io "packets received" 5
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
